

8/22/07  Description of tests in $OPIUM/testdir

This directory contains parameter files and sample results for the following
tests.  After compiling the opium program use the script "run" to cycle
through these tests.  

al
au
b
c
ca
cu
fe
h
hf
ir
la
li
mn_spd
mn_dsp
n
ne
o
p
pt
rh
s
te
ti
y_spdsp
y_ssppd

Here are some comments about each test:

1) Al - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential.  [Loginfo] keyblock is included
to show how to plot log. derivs (only works available for non-relativistic DFT psps).

2) Au - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, optimized pseudopotential, scalar-relativistic

3) B  - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, optimized pseudopotential 

4) C  - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, optimized pseudopotential, finer grid

5) Ca - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, semicore, designed-non-local pseudopotential 

6) Cu - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential 

7) Fe - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, optimized pseudopotential, finer grid, partial core correction

8) H  - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential

9) Hf - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential, scalar-relativistic

10) Ir - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential, scalar-relativistic, unbound f-state

11) La - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, semicore, optimized pseudopotential, scalar-relativistic, bound f-state

12) Li - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, semicore, optimized pseudopotential

13) Mn_spd, Mn_dsp - HF, optimized pseudopotential, smoothing on (3), this test exists to show that
HF psps are independent of the order of the valence orbitals.

14) N - HF, Troullier-Martins pseudopotential, smoothing on (1)

15) Ne - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, optimized pseudopotential 

16) O - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential, unbound d-state

17) P - HF, optimized pseudopotential, smoothing on (3)

18) Pt - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, optimized pseudopotential, scalar- relativistic, finer grid

19) Rh - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, designed non-local  pseudopotential, scalar-relativistic, finer grid

20) S - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential, unbound d-state

21) Te - HF, optimized pseudopotential, smoothing on (3), scalar-relativistic

22) Ti - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, semicore, optimized pseudopotential

23) Y_spdsp, Y_ssppd - DFT/ Wu-Cohen GGA, semicore, optimized pseudopotential, scalar-relativistic, fine 
convergence tolerance, this test exists to show that DFT psps are independent of order of the valence
states.


